    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, remove the <strong>coconut cream</strong> from the sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and chop it roughly </p>\n<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong>,<strong> tamarind paste</strong>,<strong> chopped coconut cream</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p>\n<p>Add the<strong> diced tomatoes </strong>and<strong> coconut stock</strong> and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the cauliflower is cooked through and the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency – this is your <strong>Malabar Cauliflower curry</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
